<p class="text-base">The highest level <a href="//en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Sport_of_athletics#Racewalking" target="_blank">@svg('globe', 'text-brand-icon') Racewalking <x-ui.icons.link /></a> competitions occurs at the <a href="//en.wikipedia.org/wiki/World_Athletics_Championships" target="_blank">@svg('globe', 'text-brand-icon') World Athletics Championships (formerly IAAF World Championships in Athletics <x-ui.icons.link /></a> and at the <a href="//en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Summer_Olympic_Games" target="_blank">@svg('globe', 'text-brand-icon') Summer Olympics <x-ui.icons.link /></a>, although the sport also has its own separate major competition – the <a href="//en.wikipedia.org/wiki/IAAF_World_Race_Walking_Cup" target="_blank">@svg('globe', 'text-brand-icon') IAAF World Race Walking Cup <x-ui.icons.link /></a> – which has been held since 1961. The <a href="" target="_blank">@svg('globe', 'text-brand-icon') IAAF World Race Walking Challenge <x-ui.icons.link /></a> forms the primary seasonal competition – athletes earn points for their performances at ten selected racewalking competitions and the highest scoring walkers are entered into that year's <a href="//en.wikipedia.org/wiki/IAAF_Race_Walking_Challenge_Final" target="_blank">@svg('globe', 'text-brand-icon') IAAF Race Walking Challenge Final <x-ui.icons.link /></a>.</p>
